				"id": "ALAS2-2024-2494",
				"title": "Amazon Linux 2 2017.12 - ALAS2-2024-2494: medium priority package update for c-ares",
				"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2024-25629:\n\tc-ares is a C library for asynchronous DNS requests. `ares__read_line()` is used to parse local configuration files such as `/etc/resolv.conf`, `/etc/nsswitch.conf`, the `HOSTALIASES` file, and if using a c-ares version prior to 1.27.0, the `/etc/hosts` file. If any of these configuration files has an embedded `NULL` character as the first character in a new line, it can lead to attempting to read memory prior to the start of the given buffer which may result in a crash. This issue is fixed in c-ares 1.27.0. No known workarounds exist.\n",
